            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1968-06-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1968-06-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="78"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d78">
                <head>78. Presidential Determination No. 68–12<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d78fn1">Source: Johnson Library, National Security File, Subject
                        File, Presidential Determination, Vol. IV [1 of 2], Box 40. No
                        classification marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1968-06-29">June 29, 1968</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">MEMORANDUM FOR THE SECRETARY OF STATE</p>
                <p>Determination pursuant to Section 2(c) of the Migration and Refugee Assistance
                    Act of 1962 (the “Act”)<note n="2" xml:id="d78fn2">The Migration and Refugee
                        Assistance Act of 1962, P.L. 87–510, approved on June 28, 1962. (76 Stat
                        121)</note> authorizing the transfer of up to $1,800,000 of funds made
                    available for use under the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961, as amended.<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d78fn3">The Foreign Assistance Act of 1961, P.L. 87–195,
                        approved on September 4, 1961. (75 Stat. 424)</note>
                </p>
                <p>In order to meet unexpected urgent refugee and migration needs arising in
                    connection with assistance to Cuban refugees in the United States, I hereby
                    determine, pursuant to Section 2(c) of the Act that it is important to the
                    national interest that up to $1,800,000 of funds made available for use in
                    fiscal year 1968 under the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961, as amended, be
                    transferred to and consolidated with funds made available to the Department of
                    Health, Education, and Welfare for this Act.</p>
                <p>The Secretary of State is authorized to direct the transfer of funds for this
                    purpose from appropriation accounts under the Foreign Assistance <pb facs="0261"
                        n="227" xml:id="pg_227"/> Act of 1961, as amended. The Secretary of Health,
                    Education, and Welfare is authorized to consolidate the funds so transferred
                    with funds made available to the Department of Health, Education, and Welfare
                    for this Act.</p>
                <p>The Secretary of State is requested to inform the appropriate committees of
                    Congress of this determination and the transfer of funds made under this
                    authority.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JLB1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Lyndon B. Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
